  "prompt": "If a guy stares into your eyes, follows you, tries to be near you, and copies your body language, does he have feelings for you?",
  "response": "It\u2019s possible that this behavior could indicate he has feelings for you, but it\u2019s not definitive. Here\u2019s a breakdown of what these actions might mean:\n\n1. **Staring into your eyes**: Prolonged eye contact can be a sign of interest or attraction, as it often signifies a desire to connect or engage with someone.\n\n2. **Following you or trying to be near you**: This could suggest he wants to spend time with you or be close to you, which might indicate attraction or interest.\n\n3. **Copying your body language**: Mirroring someone\u2019s gestures or posture is often a subconscious way people try to build rapport or show they\u2019re attuned to the other person. It can be a sign of interest or an attempt to feel more connected.\n\nHowever, it\u2019s important to consider context and other behaviors. These actions could also stem from curiosity, social awkwardness, or even something unrelated to romantic feelings. If you\u2019re interested in understanding his intentions, pay attention to other cues, like how he communicates, treats you, or interacts with others. If you\u2019re comfortable, you could also ask him directly about his feelings.",
